FBIS3-17626 "drsov059_f_94024" FBIS-SOV-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 27 Mar 1994 National Affairs Equality in Russia-Ukraine-Crimea Triangle Sought LD2703184194 Moscow NTV in Russian 1700 GMT 27 Mar 94 LD2703184194 Moscow NTV Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] [Passage omitted] [Unidentified correspondent] Here is how President Yuriy Meshkov sees relations with Ukraine and Russia. In an exclusive interview with NTV today he said: [Begin Meshkov recording, shown seated at desk in front of unrecognized flag] For the time being what we are proposing is a kind of legislative initiative. We are appealing to Russia and Ukraine to reach agreement on a problem which is common to all. The initiative has been accepted by the Russian side and is being worked on actively, but unfortunately there has so far been no reaction from the leadership in Kiev. How does Crimea see herself in this triangle? Of course we would like to have an equilateral triangle, although of course the scale is incompatible. [end recording] [passage omitted]
